CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 6, 1954, pg. 30 reads: "Dance To Aid Polio Drive - Teen-age members of Hill City's Welfare Department and their friends held a dance at the Centre Avenue YMCA last Friday and with the proceeds presented a $50 check to the National Foundation for the Prevention of Infantile Paralysis..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of teenagers, including members of Hill City's Welfare Department, including young woman wearing light colored short sleeved shirt with cut-outs along collar, gathered for Polio Drive dance in Centre Avenue YMCA
